export default MySelect;
```

In this example, we are using the `componentDidMount` method to access the DOM node of the container by its id and then remove the `unselectable` attribute. This method works similarly to the previous example, but it is used in class-based components.

Both approaches achieve the same goal of removing the `unselectable` attribute from the container with the arrow icon in your react component. You can choose the method that best fits your component structure and coding preferences.

Another way to remove the `unselectable` attribute is by using the `useLayoutEffect` hook in a functional component. Here's an example of how you can do it:

```jsx
